This paper deals with methods for reasoning under uncertainty in machine learning, which is a common topic in several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on deep learning and regression algorithms suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of neural networks for time series forecasting and model-based reinforcement learning tasks suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories. The mention of feedforward and recurrent neural networks suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the mention of model-based reinforcement learning suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) may be a relevant sub-category as well.
